.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-CHANNEL-STATS" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-channel-stats \- show channel counts grouped by state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-channel-stats
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns the total channel count, breakdown by state, and total active capacity.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"total_channels":N, "by_state":{...}, "total_active_capacity_msat":N}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-channel-count (1),
.BR lightning-node-channel-summary (1)
